76561198111654939,Recommended,272040,32954562,Posted: 28 June,all,ospond,"Kamiis a minimalist puzzle game, with a simple mechanic and a typical mobile interface. The goal of every puzzle is to get the board to a single color in the fewest number of moves.Kami ramps up appropriately, exploring various types of boards and helping you figure out new tricks and strategies. The puzzles are a nice blend of thinking through conceptually (what strategy should I use in deciding where to click?) and just clicking somewhere to see what happens. The puzzles can get fairly difficult, forcing you to change your plan of attack when it isn't working. Only one puzzle felt completely impossible; I tried it for an hour after beating the rest of the game but  finally gave up and used the hints. At the other end of the spectrum, maybe 30-50% of the puzzles are very easy, requiring one or two attempts.Except for the level I couldn't solve, perfecting all the levels took about 7 hours. This is long enough to include a substantial amount of content, but not so long for the levels to feel repetitive or tedoius.The atmosphere, graphics, and experience are smooth, with care put into the details. For example, the game allows you to click again while one click is still playing out -- this is really a no-brainer, but too many games don't have such features.Cons: First, I would have appreciated some steam achievements for the game. Second, at least two later levels were solvable in fewer moves than the ""perfect"" solution; I personally would have appreciated the extra challenge. Finally, there is the minor annoyance that pressing ESC puts the game into small windowed mode instead of quitting (I'll get used to it)."
,Recommended,272040,33680560,Posted: 20 July,all,Nokia 3210,"Kami delivers all that I expected when I bought the game. The gameplay feels good, the controls are perfect. But, Why I'm saying this? Because there are a bunch of ported games from IOS and Android that have clunky controls, lack of undo and reset button, slow transitions/animations, and some waste a lot of time in load a new level or restart the level.About the puzzle itself, some of them can be really tough but you can purchase a hint to make the first move, and this helps a lot when you don't know what color and segment switch.- My only concern is the lack of achievements and trading cards, some people find this pointless but for me, this gives the game more value to my purchase, I would love to craft some badges and complete 100% of the game."
