76561198107232803,Recommended,272040,8838776,"Posted: 24 January, 2014",all,Jeffrey Bosboom,"This is a puzzle game played on labeled planar graphs.  On each move, you relabel a vertex, then merge it with any neighboring vertex with the same label.  The goal is to reduce the graph to a single vertex in the fewest possible moves.  Describing it in those terms doesn't sound as fun, but I find the puzzles are much easier to solve when considered as graphs instead of the pretty-but-extraneous 2D layout.This is a mobile port, but works well on Windows 8 touch devices (I play on a Surface Pro 2).  The game initially shipped without a close button (don't need it on Android/iOS), but that was quickly remedied.  You will occasionally be asked to rate the game, but other than that there aren't any mobile problems."
