,Recommended,272040,16787811,"Posted: 29 June, 2015",all,McFrugal,"This is how KAMI works:  Click on a square to assign it a new color, and all connecting squares of that color will change too.  Change it to the color of squares near that group, and you can change those squares next move too, as they're now the same color.  Do this until the whole area is one color.There is a surprising amount of depth to the game, but I didn't have a lot of trouble with it.  Also, the last 9 ""premium"" (free expansion) levels seemed to be random garbage.  Even so on a couple of those levels I got UNDER the perfect score, which seems like it shouldn't be possible.  Maybe those levels weren't very polished.  I feel as though a bigger playing area could have added some needed challenge and enabled more varied puzzle designs.It's very pretty too, but I wouldn't pay 4 bucks for this.  Get it on sale."
